<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{suru}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{suru}} can be used to indicate that someone or something has a permanent attribute.
In the main clause @HI{{suru}} appears in the continuous form, @HI{{shiteiru}}, but in a relative
clause the @Vta{{}} form may be used instead.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{ocean^child}}ha@KJ{{long}}i@KJ{{leg}}woshiteimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yoko has long legs.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

